rComments: A great professor who is often said to being a "tricky professor". I won't agree entirely on that statement but it is clear you need to know more than what is presented. He is passionate, funny, very personable, and insightful. You will not do well if you constantly skip classes, and be prepared to do a lot of studying for the tests and quizzes.

A genius professor ,with the ability to simplify course material for a simpleton to comprehend. You are guaranteed to learn and retain information for the rest of your life.I recommend all students  regardless of their program take a course with Dr Schillachi it will be an experience of a life time

Prof. Schillaci is a fantastic, passionate lecturer. There's nothing better than a prof that loves what they do! His material is difficult, and he does push you to work hard, but I'd take any of his courses again!
Super easy to talk to

He is honestly the best professor there is! He's not too easy and not too hard. Him and our TA were nice enough to put in extra hours for our learning. As long as you attend classes and get a hands on experience with the bones, you should easily get an 80 or higher. He gives many  helpful ways of remembering things too!
Amazing prof and amazing class if you loved ANTA01! Such a nice and helpful prof and really cute! He looks like George Clooney!

I really liked Schillachi. He is kind and helpful during his office hours and practically goes through all the readings in the lectures so as long as you attend his classes and put in a reasonable amount of effort you will at least get a B. He's also really cute for an older guy!
One of the beast professor in UTSC. Amazing lecture style.
Amazing professor. One of the best lecturers I have had.

He's a great teacher. You really need to memorize a lot of genus' and species, so don't take the class if you can't do that. He covers the text in class, I didn't even buy the book and got a mark in the 80's. Great class if you are into primatology.

B14 is hard work if it's not something you're used to, but his lectures are really informative and he makes it interesting with his enthusiasm. pay attention in class and be sure to memorize. ps.. hes totally gorgeous!
Very good professor. You actually learn alot from his lectures.
Amazing prof! Keep it up!

Every year I have 1-2 classes with Schillaci. Simply put, aside from Sawchuk, he's one of the best profs on campus. This course was also very interesting. It was the first time being offered, so I recommend it highly!
Extremely nice guy.  Very Helpful.  Great prof, explains well. Genuine enthusiasm for course material.  Keeps you interested.

I wouldn't say it was the greatest experience. The midterm was tricky, his jeopardy questions were strange but ok. The short answer was more difficult. final wasn't too bad. The zoo project is interesting, recommended course!
Actually I did great in the class my mark was good but still writing about him because this type of proff is unacceptable ...

get 2 no ur profs 1st b4 pointing fingers n makin childish judgements. u'll be surprised in the end. Like i said i've had poor marks with him but does not make him a horrible person...blame urself for ur own mistakes rather than pointin ur fingers on others.u'd b surprised with the amount of time he spends on helpin and supervising his students!

As a student, and from experience, I find it very unfair to rate professors in terms of a poor mark. I have had Schillaci as a professor in other courses and I still came out with a very poor mark! Determining his status as a professor or writing to the administration and get him fired because of a poor mark is unacceptable. You should get to know

I went into my exam for ANTB14 with a 70 percent. I came out with 44%. I was shocked. That means I got a 6% as a final mark. 10% of the final was based on using correct English. My English isn't horrible. But 6% is just very stressing to deal with. The TAs misscalculated my mid-term, my quiz, and now my final.

A very helpful and enthusiastic prof. I learned so much from his C47 course, it's unbelievable. I've had him as a prof for the past 4 years, and I always enjoy his classes. He's hot but the midterm was crazy crazy hard
helpful, prepared, funny. posts up his slides as well as his notes so that students don't have to spend so much time writing in class, which is very helpful.
Awesome professor. Passionate about the subject. Best part: He's American and loves monkeys!
very hard class, midterm was tricky, the final was worst, the material was interesting but his evaluation methods were ridiculous (the midterm and final were each worth 45%)
He was really hard. His exams were tricky even if the required reading is done.

Necessary tools for this class: a photographic memory and an inability to get bored. The midterm and final were multiple choice with deliberately misleading questions (41% of the class got lower than 55% on the midterm). Lectures consist of him reading off slides and demonstrating simple ideas in complicated ways. Avoid this prof/class.

Prof. Schillaci is one of the best prof's at U of T. He goes out of his way to help students advance in their educational goals.  He's donated endless hours of time supervising those of us who actually care about the work that we do. He provides his students with interesting ways to advance academically, for which I am appreciative

I tried so hard for this course, put so much time into it but it turned out to be the worst mark I got this semester. The first lab quizz and midterm were easy, but the second lab quizz was brutal(average:55) and the final exam was 3 essays. For quizzes, if you even know the stuff very well, you will not have time, stupid bellringers, awfull course

This class was horrible! He refused to tell us how much our last 2 tests were weighted, which was ridiculous. He lied to us regarding the weighting of our tests. Prof. Schillaci is the worst professor at UTSC. He's unfair, he's lazy, unreliable, unhelpful and lacks proper communication skills. He doesn't show up for his office hours, he doesn't grade students' assignments fairly and his teaching is horrendous. He doesn't give proper examples and he doesn't outline his expectations for students at all.

It was a nice course; not my cup of tea, though, so that was hard to get over.  He really tired to make it interesting, even though the course wasn't.  The exams nearly killed me, so beware of those.  STUDY EVERYTHING!
Dismissive, lame, and of no help. :(

clear, concise, and funny
he's a good prof .... but it was hard to get a hold of him

He's a good prof, very helpful and good-looking.  Exams are fair---study and you will get a good mark.  He sometimes is unclear about what will be on the exams, so study the text and lecture notes very well.

I think he's a really good prof, he is approachable, and interesting - a little too much emphasis on his research, but i find it interesting.  Sometimes he seems to lose the class because they are busy talking amongst themselves, and has to repeat simple concepts which can be annoying.
love the class, talks about himself too much, as well with his slide shows of his trips...
